1
00:01:30,670 --> 00:01:34,970
[Deep Lurk]

2
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,800
[Episode 30]

3
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:27,230
As expected,

4
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,829
it wasn't just Ling Han at the scene yesterday.

5
00:02:30,430 --> 00:02:31,710
Mi Lan and Zong Fang were here too.

6
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,190
I'm heading back now.

7
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:37,790
-Okay.
-I'll treat you to drinks sometime.

8
00:02:38,070 --> 00:02:39,150
Don't forget!

9
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:39,750
I won't.

10
00:02:39,770 --> 00:02:40,540
Alright, I'm off.

11
00:02:41,290 --> 00:02:42,090
Leader Wen.

12
00:02:45,380 --> 00:02:46,700
Mi Lan and Zong Fang have been found.

13
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:57,350
Young Master.

14
00:02:58,510 --> 00:02:59,310
Young Master.

15
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:00,430
It's here.

16
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:02,710
Someone ordered ten days' worth of meals from Defengxuan Restaurant,

17
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,350
requesting two deliveries per day.

18
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:05,360
But

19
00:03:05,380 --> 00:03:07,440
the delivery guy never saw the person inside.

20
00:03:07,710 --> 00:03:08,550
Every time,

21
00:03:08,550 --> 00:03:09,630
he just knocked twice,

22
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,400
left the food container, and walked away immediately.

23
00:03:11,790 --> 00:03:13,640
This was specifically instructed by the person who placed the order.

24
00:03:14,350 --> 00:03:16,390
The house was bought by Bai Qingkui's bodyguard,

25
00:03:16,390 --> 00:03:17,079
Liu.

26
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:18,500
It went through several hands before that.

27
00:03:18,690 --> 00:03:20,020
After the purchase, it remained vacant,

28
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,079
with no one living there.

29
00:03:21,110 --> 00:03:22,829
Some time ago, Bai Qingkui moved in,

30
00:03:22,829 --> 00:03:24,510
and rumor has it he died there.

31
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:26,030
Recently, someone else moved in.

32
00:03:26,030 --> 00:03:27,829
But my men couldn't figure out who they are.

33
00:03:27,890 --> 00:03:28,810
They didn't dare get too close

34
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,640
and never saw their faces.

35
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:30,750
Sorry, Young Master.

36
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:31,690
I didn't handle this well for you.

37
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:33,829
It's fine.

38
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:34,990
You've already done great

39
00:03:35,060 --> 00:03:35,990
tracking them this far

40
00:03:36,010 --> 00:03:37,190
without being discovered.

41
00:03:37,430 --> 00:03:38,350
When you go back,

42
00:03:38,350 --> 00:03:39,390
tell your men

43
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:40,230
to keep their mouths shut.

44
00:03:40,230 --> 00:03:41,310
We can't afford any trouble.

45
00:03:41,310 --> 00:03:42,030
Understood.

46
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:42,790
Young Master,

47
00:03:42,790 --> 00:03:43,560
how about

48
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,950
the two of us stay and help you out?

49
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,300
The people inside

50
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:49,900
are extremely dangerous.

51
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:52,110
The two of you won't be of much help.

52
00:03:52,230 --> 00:03:53,990
If they take you hostage,

53
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:55,079
I'll have to save you as well.

54
00:03:56,910 --> 00:03:58,680
Alright, Rat, Gangzi.

55
00:03:58,910 --> 00:04:00,180
Don't you trust my skills?

56
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:00,690
Let's go.

57
00:04:01,860 --> 00:04:02,990
-Be careful, then.
-We're leaving.

58
00:04:08,270 --> 00:04:08,910
Dao,

59
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:11,950
you should go too.

60
00:04:11,990 --> 00:04:12,790
Young Master,

61
00:04:13,510 --> 00:04:14,750
are you joking?

62
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:16,350
How can I leave at a time like this?

63
00:04:16,550 --> 00:04:17,350
Enough.

64
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:18,870
This time, listen to me.

65
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,250
You're someone who does great things.

66
00:04:20,470 --> 00:04:21,829
Your life is precious.

67
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:22,970
Besides,

68
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:25,500
we still need you to take charge of saving Second Young Master.

69
00:04:26,710 --> 00:04:27,830
I'll cover the back door.

70
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:28,750
You knock on the front.

71
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,310
Take this dagger for self-defense.

72
00:04:36,470 --> 00:04:38,300
Just hold them off until Wen Yeming arrives.

73
00:04:39,110 --> 00:04:40,030
Don't risk your life.

74
00:04:41,090 --> 00:04:42,130
Why are you talking so much?

75
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:03,010
Who is it?

76
00:05:04,990 --> 00:05:07,950
I'm from Defengxuan Restaurant, delivering your meal.

77
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,770
The money you left outside earlier was too much.

78
00:05:10,790 --> 00:05:12,030
I didn't dare take it.

79
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:15,470
Something is wrong.

80
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:17,510
It's Yun Hongqi.

81
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:29,320
Mi Lan!

82
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:10,670
This stab

83
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:13,470
is for my grandma.

84
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:15,070
Today,

85
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:19,150
I'll make you pay for your blood debts.

86
00:06:32,230 --> 00:06:33,230
That stab earlier

87
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,840
was something I owed you.

88
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:36,350
From now on,

89
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:38,320
I won't give you another chance like that.

90
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:16,750
You said

91
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:18,830
you'd treat me well

92
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,720
and give me a home.

93
00:07:22,350 --> 00:07:23,350
But now,

94
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:28,180
you're trying to kill me.

95
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:30,750
Your love

96
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:34,060
is just that much.

97
00:08:32,190 --> 00:08:32,950
Are you okay?

98
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:33,710
I'm fine.

99
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,159
Yun Hongqi has been knocked out.

100
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:35,990
Go save him now.

101
00:08:36,010 --> 00:08:36,929
I'll chase after Zong Fang.

102
00:08:55,980 --> 00:08:57,870
[Nurses' Station]

103
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,980
You're way too impatient.

104
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,650
With just the two of you,

105
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:01,450
there's no way you could catch Mi Lan and Zong Fang.

106
00:09:02,030 --> 00:09:03,750
At the very least, you should've waited for me to arrive before taking action.

107
00:09:04,030 --> 00:09:04,830
Officer Wen,

108
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:06,030
it was my mistake.

109
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:09,910
I was afraid of delays causing complications.

110
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:12,310
I think you were simply eager for revenge.

111
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:19,020
Your original plan was probably

112
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,440
to capture Zong Fang alive and kill Mi Lan,

113
00:09:20,470 --> 00:09:21,190
right?

114
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:27,110
I thought I could control myself.

115
00:09:29,190 --> 00:09:30,070
I thought

116
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:33,150
I could look at the bigger picture

117
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:35,090
and wouldn't kill her when I saw her.

118
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:37,270
But when I saw her,

119
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:38,670
I thought of my grandma,

120
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,110
and I just couldn't control myself.

121
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,680
I really wanted to kill her with my own hands.

122
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:42,350
I wanted to...

123
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:44,620
I just couldn't control myself, do you understand?

124
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,650
With your level of skill,

125
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:50,130
you're no match for someone with professional training as a special agent.

126
00:09:50,310 --> 00:09:51,390
You can't compete Mi Lan.

127
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:52,370
So what if I'm not?

128
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:00,820
You need to stay rational.

129
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,520
That's the only way to save Yun Hongshen.

130
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:09,700
How's Shen now?

131
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:34,830
We're all familiar with each other here,

132
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:37,940
so I hope our conversation can be direct and to the point.

133
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:39,830
And you know perfectly well

134
00:10:39,860 --> 00:10:40,710
what kind of person I am.

135
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:43,230
When I was fifteen,

136
00:10:44,070 --> 00:10:45,830
Uncle Yang gave me a watch

137
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:47,350
as a birthday gift.

138
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:48,590
I always kept it in

139
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:49,910
the left drawer of my desk.

140
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:51,750
So when Jingyu mentioned it,

141
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:53,790
I immediately knew Uncle Yang was looking for me.

142
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:57,450
That birthday happened to be celebrated at Xiaoxiang Restaurant,

143
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,960
so that's where we met.

144
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:02,310
What did he want?

145
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:04,470
He wanted me to leave Changsha to lay low for a while.

146
00:11:04,630 --> 00:11:05,570
Why?

147
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:07,130
You already know, don't you?

148
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:10,780
Someone accused my father and me of being communists.

149
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:19,670
How do you explain this?

150
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:34,510
This must be something Ling Han prepared for me.

151
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:37,200
He wants to use this to cement his accusations that I'm a communist.

152
00:11:41,990 --> 00:11:42,590
Did Jingyu

153
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:46,480
die at the location mentioned in this newspaper clipping?

154
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:47,750
What are you trying to say?

155
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:50,390
Ling Han,

156
00:11:52,290 --> 00:11:53,260
it's you again.

157
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:55,590
Just wait.

158
00:11:56,570 --> 00:11:57,650
I'll kill you for sure!

159
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,990
I don't want to hear this right now.

160
00:11:59,070 --> 00:11:59,790
I just want to know

161
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:01,610
what organization your father truly serves?

162
00:12:02,070 --> 00:12:02,870
I think

163
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:06,060
you should ask Ling Han instead

164
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,680
which organization he's truly loyal to.

165
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:26,480
Sir.

166
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:35,050
Uncle Yang,

167
00:12:37,470 --> 00:12:39,080
Jingyu was killed by Ling Han.

168
00:12:41,230 --> 00:12:41,810
Come.

169
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:44,000
For all those young lives

170
00:12:45,070 --> 00:12:47,150
like Jingyu's.

171
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,640
For their courage

172
00:12:58,410 --> 00:12:59,320
and kindness.

173
00:13:31,990 --> 00:13:33,830
Stop making futile efforts.

174
00:13:34,540 --> 00:13:37,280
My plan has already been set in motion.

175
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:48,740
It's my mistake.

176
00:13:49,510 --> 00:13:51,070
I should bear the consequences.

177
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,800
The issue with the gold reserves

178
00:14:04,430 --> 00:14:05,470
involves too many people.

179
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:06,790
You don't understand the situation,

180
00:14:06,990 --> 00:14:08,060
so you can't take on this responsibility.

181
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:14,380
Let's think of another way.

182
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:22,800
There's no time left.

183
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,800
Our cause needs someone to continue it.

184
00:14:29,190 --> 00:14:30,070
Don't worry.

185
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:31,830
Our cause

186
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:33,710
will definitely be carried forward by others.

187
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:04,040
Chief Ke,

188
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:08,140
if I didn't mishear just now,

189
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:09,910
are you telling me

190
00:15:10,180 --> 00:15:12,660
that they're denying it now?

191
00:15:13,790 --> 00:15:14,790
In other words,

192
00:15:15,510 --> 00:15:16,650
your investigation

193
00:15:17,590 --> 00:15:18,870
has made no progress at all?

194
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,760
At present, we don't have strong evidence.

195
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:25,150
And given their special identities,

196
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:26,310
there are too many eyes on them.

197
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:27,980
It's not suitable to take extreme measures.

198
00:15:29,460 --> 00:15:31,220
Then you might as well let them go,

199
00:15:31,530 --> 00:15:32,700
apologize to them,

200
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:35,190
admit we made a mistake,

201
00:15:35,470 --> 00:15:36,780
and say sorry.

202
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:42,640
Right now, it's undoubtedly putting the Director under immense pressure.

203
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,080
Ke Jingping, I'm telling you,

204
00:15:51,530 --> 00:15:54,780
you must come up with something...

205
00:15:55,990 --> 00:15:58,910
Some kind of excuse to get through this.

206
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:00,570
Understood.

207
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:08,780
Hello?

208
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:12,550
Why is it always someone looking for you?

209
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:15,180
Hello?

210
00:16:15,870 --> 00:16:16,490
Chief.

211
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:19,130
There may be more to Yang Ziming's true identity than meets the eye.

212
00:16:24,070 --> 00:16:24,720
Director Gong.

213
00:16:26,630 --> 00:16:27,260
Minister Yang,

214
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:29,030
our Chief requests your presence.

215
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,200
I've checked your family's call records.

216
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:26,829
The morning before Zhang Xiancheng arrived in Changsha,

217
00:17:26,859 --> 00:17:29,320
you received a phone call from Shanghai.

218
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:31,390
I'd like to know who called you

219
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:33,180
and what the conversation was about.

220
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:37,920
When I left Shanghai, it was in a hurry.

221
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:39,190
So,

222
00:17:39,370 --> 00:17:41,490
I didn't have time to deal with my property in Shanghai.

223
00:17:41,610 --> 00:17:43,290
I entrusted a real estate agent

224
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,240
to sell my house.

225
00:17:45,270 --> 00:17:47,500
That call was from the agent,

226
00:17:47,570 --> 00:17:48,920
and it was about the property.

227
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:50,350
A phone call

228
00:17:50,370 --> 00:17:51,820
about a property at as early as 5 a.m.?

229
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:53,710
What kind of inconsiderate agent

230
00:17:53,710 --> 00:17:54,710
would pass muster with someone

231
00:17:54,710 --> 00:17:56,310
as discerning as you, Minister Yang?

232
00:17:56,830 --> 00:17:58,420
The transfer order came unexpectedly.

233
00:17:58,580 --> 00:17:59,420
In a rush,

234
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:01,120
I didn't have enough time

235
00:18:01,260 --> 00:18:03,450
to carefully select a proper agent.

236
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,770
And wouldn't you know it,

237
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:08,390
on the very morning you took that call,

238
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:11,330
No. 76 captured a Communist liaison officer

239
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,990
who had infiltrated Shanghai from Northern Jiangsu

240
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,000
on a secret mission.

241
00:18:15,670 --> 00:18:16,970
There was an exchange of gunfire,

242
00:18:17,420 --> 00:18:19,210
and the liaison officer was killed on the spot.

243
00:18:19,230 --> 00:18:20,050
However,

244
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:23,700
the contact tasked with meeting him survived

245
00:18:23,990 --> 00:18:25,010
and defected.

246
00:18:25,060 --> 00:18:26,380
According to this defector,

247
00:18:26,830 --> 00:18:28,270
their mission to Shanghai

248
00:18:28,530 --> 00:18:30,320
was to receive a shipment of gold.

249
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:37,460
The Communists are that capable?

250
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,880
Under the noses of the Japanese,

251
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,940
with both the NBIS and the CBIS watching,

252
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:45,030
they still managed to secure gold?

253
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:45,870
Yes.

254
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:48,280
At such a difficult time,

255
00:18:48,630 --> 00:18:50,100
they were able to perform a sleight of hand

256
00:18:50,370 --> 00:18:51,490
and fool the Japanese.

257
00:18:51,730 --> 00:18:53,690
The person who pulled this off must be quite a genius.

258
00:18:55,150 --> 00:18:55,950
Someone, perhaps,

259
00:18:57,030 --> 00:18:58,900
like your friend Yun Muzhi.

260
00:18:59,230 --> 00:19:00,030
Chief Ke,

261
00:19:00,370 --> 00:19:02,090
you're confusing me with your words.

262
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:04,540
Who performed a sleight of hand?

263
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,070
And how is Muzhi

264
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:08,390
involved in this?

265
00:19:10,990 --> 00:19:12,030
As far as I know,

266
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,760
the Bank of France handed over a shipment

267
00:19:15,090 --> 00:19:16,790
of gold to the Japanese.

268
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:18,860
But when it reached Japan,

269
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,340
it had all turned into lead ingots.

270
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:22,920
Is that so?

271
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:27,200
Well, that's certainly satisfying to hear!

272
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:29,260
Why should we

273
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:31,150
let the Japanese take our gold?

274
00:19:31,150 --> 00:19:32,310
You're right.

275
00:19:32,630 --> 00:19:34,280
But on the other hand,

276
00:19:34,470 --> 00:19:36,400
Minister Yang,

277
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:37,790
you approve of the sleight-of-hand with that gold, don't you?

278
00:19:39,620 --> 00:19:40,350
Chief Ke,

279
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:42,100
that's not fair of you.

280
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:44,090
You're twisting the facts.

281
00:19:44,430 --> 00:19:46,400
No matter how I answer, I'll be in the wrong,

282
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:47,580
won't I?

283
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:48,950
I'd like to ask,

284
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:52,150
if this question were directed at you, Chief Ke,

